---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Donate from "../components/Donate.astro";
import Contact from "../components/Contact.astro";
import NowPlaying from "../components/NowPlaying.svelte";
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:py-16">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.35fr_0.95fr] lg:gap-10">
      <div class="min-w-0 space-y-6">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1
            class="max-w-3xl text-balance text-3xl font-black tracking-tight text-base-content sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
          >
            Heyo, I'm Emily~
          </h1>
          <p
            class="max-w-2xl text-pretty text-base leading-7 text-base-content/80 sm:text-lg"
          >
            I'm an indie developer from South Australia. I'm currently studying <strong
              >Game Development</strong
            > alongside completing my <strong
              >South Australian Certificate of Education</strong
            > I enjoy doing <strong>photography</strong> and have had the opportunity
            to work as a photographer for a youth-focused music and arts centre!
          </p>
          <p
            class="max-w-2xl text-pretty text-base leading-7 text-base-content/80 sm:text-lg"
          >
            I have a wide knowledge of different programming languages,
            including a proficiency in <strong>Python</strong> and functional expertise
            in <strong>C#</strong>, <strong>Go</strong>, <strong
              >Typescript</strong
            >, I also have practical experience with <strong>Lua</strong>.
          </p>
          <p
            class="max-w-2xl text-pretty text-base leading-7 text-base-content/80 sm:text-lg"
          >
            I believe in a future where <strong>AI</strong> can be ethically to assist
            developers when the right rules are applied, in my opinion AI should not
            be treated as a <i>"true"</i> developer and should be an assistant to
            help developers with pre-existing knowledge build content like UI quicker,
            although I'm against the concept of "autonomous agents" otherwise known
            as vibe coding as there's no true oversight or review of what the AI might
            be building.
          </p>
          <p
            class="max-w-2xl text-pretty text-base leading-7 text-base-content/80 sm:text-lg"
          >
            I believe in a more federated and decentralised future and currently
            self-host my own <a
              class="link font-bold"
              href="https://forgejo.org/">Forgejo</a
            > server under <a class="link" href="https://forge.kemonomimi.moe"
              >Kemonoforge</a
            >, a <a class="link font-bold" href="https://gotosocial.org/"
              >GoToSocial</a
            > under <a class="link" href="https://social.kemonomimi.moe"
              >Kemonosocial</a
            >, and <a class="link font-bold" href="https://matrix.org">Matrix</a
            > under <a class="link" href="https://chat.kemonomimi.moe"
              >Kemonochat</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="min-w-0 flex flex-col gap-4">
        <NowPlaying client:load />
        <Contact />
        <Donate />
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
